<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--FatalFestival     03-07 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Fatal Festival,0146</SECOND>
<HEAD>At Least 25 Die While Worshiping Destruction God</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 25 Hindu pilgrims were reported
killed in a stampede and a separate building collapse during the
Hindu festival that celebrates the birthday of Shiva, the faith's
god of destruction.
   Twenty people died Monday near Patna, capital of Bihar state, of
suffocation during a stampede as people rushed to a shrine to
worship, The Press Trust of India news agency reported.
   Five pilgrims died at Ginar in Gujarat state in the partial
collapse of a building containing a Shiva idol, news reports said.
   Millions of Hindus across India celebrated the festival,
believing Shiva will ensure well-being.
   People rush to shrines on festival days to offer flowers in a
ritual of worship, causing periodic stampedes because idols are
normally located within enclosed spaces or rooms.
</TEXT>
