<HEAD>Air Force Launches Unarmed Minuteman Missile</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VANDENBERG AIR FORCE BASE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Air Force launched
an unarmed Minuteman III missile early today, filling the night sky
with brilliant light as it streaked toward a missile range 4,200
miles away.
   The launch at 12:26 a.m. was the third of 13 launches scheduled
for this year from this base 140 miles northwest of downtown Los
Angeles, said Col. Richard Hill.
   ``Everything looked good,'' he said.
   The intercontinental ballistic missile reached its target on the
Kwajalein Missile Range in the Marshall Islands after a 30-minute
flight, Hill said.
   The missile was launched by the 91st Strategic Missile Wing,
based at Minot Air Force Base in North Dakota, he said.
