<FIRST>r i AM-Korea     03-07 0263</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Korea,0268</SECOND>
<HEAD>North Korea Accuses South Korea of Firing at Border Post</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Bombing Trial, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   North Korea accused South Korean troops of firing
machine guns Tuesday at a guard post on the North Korean side of the
border and contended it was part of attempts to start a new war.
   Pyongyang's official Korean Central News Agency, monitored in
Tokyo, said the firing ``gravely threatened the safety of civilian
policemen of our side on routine duty,'' and said their patience
prevented the incident from developing into an armed conflict.
   It said the firing occurred Tuesday morning in the central sector
of the border area between North Korea and South Korea.
   ``The gun firing, timed to coincide with the aggressive `Team
Spirit '89' joint military maneuvers staged by the U.S. imperialists
and the South Korean puppets, shipping huge aggressive forces and
destruction weapons into South Korea, vividly shows how frantically
they are trying to unleash a new war by aggravating the situation on
the Korean peninsula,'' the agency said.
   North Korea has demanded cancellation of the Team Spirit exercise
this month, saying it makes progress in a Korean dialogue
impossible. U.S. and South Korean officials say the annual military
exercise _ in which about 200,000 U.S. and South Korean troops are
involved _ is purely defensive.
   North Korea suspended talks between legislators of both countries
in protest of the military exercise. Other talks aimed at arranging
the first meeting between both sides' prime ministers also have
bogged down because of Team Spirit, but another session is set for
April 12.
</TEXT>
