   And that is _ that is, never get all too up-tight about _ about
stuff that hasn't reached Lubbock yet, and be sure that there's some
accomplishments going on _
   Q. _ in Peoria _
   A. _ accomplishments going on that people can say, ``Wait a
minute. There's quite a bit happening here.''
   Q. But, sir _ if I could follow up _ is there a danger here, sir?
Is there a potential danger if the perception lingers?
   A. You're in a better position to answer that than I am.
   However, I think _ you know, I come back to the Tower thing.
   I think people are fair.
   They are not making up their minds _ on perceptions _ make them
up on facts.
   And, I am one who felt that way coming out of the campaign.
   That's why I go back to that.
   It was a very important thing to me what happened after about a
year ago and what _ you know, here I stand here.
   And so, I don't think the American people make up their minds on
perceptions.
   I think they make up their minds on facts.
   Now, you can have various waves of approval or disapproval, but I
think if we can just get our message out on the facts, the way I've
spelled them out here, I think we'll do fine.
   But I've _ you know _
   White House press secretary Marlin Fitzwater: It's after 11:30.
   Bush: Yeah?
