<HEAD>New Riots During Funeral of Police Shooting Victim</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Riots over police brutality broke out
Tuesday during the funeral of a man killed by police last week,
witnesses said.
   Mourners, some of whom carried signs saying ``No to police
brutality,'' attacked police trucks following the funeral, according
to the witnesses. No injuries were reported.
   The violence spread quickly as rioters attacked government
vehicles trapped in the traffic jam created by the protest,
witnesses said.
   On Friday night, police shot and killed three people after a bus
driver, fleeing a traffic police officer, ran over and killed an
elderly man.
   Last month, a court sentenced to death a policemen for the 1987
shooting of two brothers. The court ruled the murder, which started
rioting in which eight people died, was not justifiable.
