<HEAD>West German Sentenced to 10 Months for Insulting Jews</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARLSRUHE, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A court convicted a man Tuesday
and sentenced him to 10 months in jail for insulting Jews in a
pamphlet that claimed they were responsible for their fate in the
Nazi Holocaust.
   Rainer Graf Adelmann, 40, also was convicted of forming an
``anti-Semitic club.''
   Adelman wrote that Jews killed by the Hitler regime had
themselves to blame because they ``went along with Nazi laws'' and
finally ``voluntarily showed up for their own deportations.''
   Judge Hermann Frank said: ``The Jewish population and the Jewish
race has been insulted and defamed in the worst fashion.''
   Adelmann told the court he had not intended to insult anyone and
merely sought reasons for the Holocaust.
