<HEAD>AT&amp;T Creates Data Communications Subsidiary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. said Tuesday
it had created a subsidiary, AT&amp;T Paradyne, that incorporates the
data communications equipment operations of AT&amp;T and the recently
acquired Paradyne Corp.
   AT&amp;T Paradyne will be based in Largo, Fla., the headquarters of
Paradyne, which AT&amp;T announced in December it was buying for $250
million in cash. John Mitcham, who was president of Paradyne, will
also be president of the new subsidiary.
   In keeping with its decentralization drive, AT&amp;T said it will set
up the subsidiary with its own board of directors and responsibility
for profits and losses. Paradyne lost $40.2 million in the nine
months ended last Sept. 30.
