<SECOND>AM-Auto Incentives,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>GM Cranks Out New Incentives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Motors Corp. on Tuesday announced a
variety of incentives for some Chevrolet, Buick and Oldsmobile cars,
including a three-part option on some Oldsmobiles.
   The nation's largest automaker said it was offering Oldsmobile
buyers the options of low-interest financing, cash back or free
gasoline for a year with the purchase of some cars.
   The program lasts through March.
   Some Buick buyers will have the option of cash rebates or low
financing packages through April 3. Purchasers of some Chevrolets
will have that same option through May 2.
   By Tuesday afternoon, Chrysler Corp. and Ford Motor Co. had
announced no new incentives.
   Earlier in the day, though, Ford Vice Chairman Harold Poling said
his company would remain competitive with other automakers'
marketing programs.
</TEXT>
