<DOCNO> AP890307-0282 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-03-07-89 2139EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-GeneralCinema     03-07 0231</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-General Cinema,0238</SECOND>
<HEAD>General Cinema Earnings Up 63 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHESTNUT HILL, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Cinema Corp. earnings jumped
63 percent in its first quarter compared with the same quarter of
1988, spurred by a $55.7 million gain from the sale of its stock in
RJR Nabisco Inc.
   Net earnings were $44.4 milion, or 60 cents a share, compared
with $28 million, or 38 cents a share, in the same period last year,
the company said Tuesday.
   General Cinema said revenues from its beverage bottling division
and ticket sales at its movie theaters increased, but operating
profits declined due to higher soft drink promotional spending and
higher operating costs for new and larger theaters.
   Revenues for the three months ended Jan. 31 totaled $607.5
million, up 9.8 percent from the first quarter of 1988, but
operating earnings fell to $40 million from $46 a year earlier, the
company said.
   During the first quarter, Genera Cinema agreed to sell its soft
drink bottling business to Pepsico Inc. for $1.75 billion in cash,
but the transaction is subject to approval under antitrust laws by
the Federal Trade Commission. Richard Smith, General Cinema's
chairman and chief executive officer, said the deal was expected to
close by late March or early April.
   The soft drink bottling business contibuted $167.8 million in
revenue and $12.2 million in operating earnings to first-quarter
results, the company said.
</TEXT>
